column1: From 2011-12 onwards, 7 local authorities started reporting as Dorset Waste Partnership. These are Weymouth and Portland Borough Council, West Dorset District Council, Purbeck District Council, North Dorset District Council, East Dorset District Council, Christchurch Borough Council, and Dorset County Council.
From 2015/16 onwards Chiltern District Council jointly reports their waste data with Wycombe District Council.
From 2016/17 onwards, Cambridge City and South Cambridgeshire Councils jointly report their waste
From 2017/18, 6 local authorities started reporting as Somerset Waste Partnership. These are Somerset County Council, Mendip, Sedgmoor, South Somerset, Taunton Deane, West Somerset.
From 2019-20 there were several mergers and changes to local authorities:-

column2: 5 of the local authorities reporting as the 'Dorset waste Partnership': East Dorset District Council, North Dorset District council, Purbeck District Council, West Dorset district council and Weymouth and Portland Borough Council merged to become 'Dorset Council'.
Christchurch Borough Council formerly part of the 'Dorset Waste Partnership', merged with Bounemouth Borough Council and Poole Borough Council to become 'Bournemouth, Poole and Christchurch Council'.
Suffolk Coastal District Council and Waveney District Council merged to become 'East Suffolk Council'.
Forest Heath district Council and St Edmundsbury Borough Council merged to become 'West Suffolk council'.
Corby Borough Council and Kettering Borough Council now report together as 'Corby and Kettering Shared Service'

column1: From 2020-21 'Buckinhamshire County Council' disposal authority was replaced by the new 'Buckinhgamshire council' unitary authority.  Ayelsbury Vale district Council, South Bucks District Council and Wycombe District Council were absorbed into this UA and no longer report.
From 2021-22 'Northamptonshire County Council' disposal authority was replaced by two new unitary authorities:-

column2: 'North Northamptonshire' , absorbed the waste collection authorities previously reporting as 'Corby & Kettering  shared service', 'East Northamptonshire Council' and 'Wellingborough Borough Council'.
'West Northamptonshire' absorbed the waste collection authorities previously reporting as 'Daventry District Council', 'Northampton Borough Council' and 'South Northamptonshire District Council'.

column1: From 2022-23 'Mid Suffolk District Council' has been renamed  'Mid Suffolk and Babergh District Council'.  For ease of comparison, in this dataset the name has also been changed for previous years.  There are no revisions to historical figures as a result of this change.
From 2023-24 there were several mergers and changes to local authorities due to the creation of three new unitary authorities:-

column2: Allerdale Borough Council, Carlisle City Council, Copeland Borough Council, and Cumbria County Council merged to become 'Cumberland Council'.
Barrow-in-Furness Borough Council, Eden District Council, South Lakeland District Council, and Cumbria County Council merged to become 'Westmoreland and Furness Council'.

Craven District Council, Hambleton District Council, Harrogate District Council, Richmondshire District Council, Ryedale District Council, Scarborough Borough Council, and Selby District Council merged to become 'North Yorkshire Council'.
Somerset Waste Partnership has been renamed Somerset Council.

Figures shown for England and South West region for 2023/24 are provisional and may be revised in the next edition of these statistics. This is due to incomplete reporting by Bristol City Council at the time these datasets were produced.
Estimates for Bristol are included within aggregated totals for England and South West region.
